Y'all, the most amazing thing happened. I have an ear ache, so I went to Sprouts Market to get some grapefruit seed extract (natural antibiotic). The guy working in the natural health dept asked me if I had any questions. I showed him my ear and neck and he told me he's an aroma therapist. We went to the little bottles of oils and he had me smell them. Depending on what I could smell and how I liked them, he found out I'm an insulin dependent diabetic and my elevated blood pressure. He went as far as to ask me about eating yogurt and how its what's making my ear ache worse. I'm in awe, I've never had someone so spot on before. I took the cranberry pills and pine and oregano essential oils and I'm already starting to feel better!

Alot of people asked me to share my diet that's helped me with my blood sugars and weight it's called the georgina diet a diet my dr named after me  Breakfast is 2 morning star veggie links 1 egg any style 1 cup watermelon 3/4 cup bran cereal but i use any flavor special k cereal 3/4 cup 1 percent or 2 percent milk Lunch is 4 carrot sticks 1 oz cheese 1/2cup watermelon or any kind of melon you like 1 can tuna/salmon or chicken i do a special piece of cooked boneless chicken Dinner is unlimited kale salad but only 2 tbsp dressing 1 cup lentil soup but i found a healthy greens soup i like or any soup that has good amount of fiber in it make your own if you want i also have a awesome lentil and barley soup recipe my kids love that way I can control the amount of sodium in it and then a small piece of chicken i cook it and put into my kale salad along with the tomatoes and whatever other veggies i put into the salad also drink plenty of water which helps lower blood sugars i never been a big fan of plain water so I make sassy water which is 10 cups of water in a pitcher 1 cucumber peeled or unpeeled and sliced up 1 lemon sliced up a piece of ginger peeled and shredded and 12 or more mint leaves put in fridge over night drink all the next day my blood sugar was almost 11 before doing this diet was looking at having to do insulin but after working on my stress level dropping some weight my blood sugars dropped down to the low 7s  i hope this can help someone i was once told to take 200 milgrams metformin but to many side affects i only  do 500 with breakfast 500 with dinner i do the diet 5 days a week and eat sensibly on the weekends it's about fiber measuring and reading labels looking for grams of sugar for me

Quick & Easy Chicken Flautas Ingredients 2 cans (12.5 oz each) chicken, drained & flaked or bake your own 6 oz cream cheese, softened 1/3 cup salsa 1 cup shredded monterey jack cheese/or your favorite 1/4 teaspoon cumin 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 12 8" flour tortillas (I use the Mission Carb Balance) Directions Preheat oven to 400  Combine drained and flaked chicken, cream cheese, salsa, cheese, cumin, and garlic powder in a mixing bowl. Stir together until well combined Spread 3 tablespoons (a large spoonful) of chicken mixture onto a tortilla. Roll up tightly and place seam side down on a cookie sheet Repeat with remaining tortillas Spray the tops of the flautas with cooking spray. Don't soak them but you want them to have a decent coating of cooking spray so they will get really brown and crispy. I also like to sprinkle some kosher salt on top of the sprayed flautas but this is totally optional. Bake for 18-20 minutes or until they reach desired crispness that you want. Let cool for about 5-10 minutes before serving so the filling can cool and come together Shared Diabetic Recipes ##As with any recipe carb count depends on the ingredients you use so please don't ask what's the carb count##

Diabetic Cornbread Ingredients 1/4 cup oil 1/2 cup water 1 cup buttermilk 1 egg 1 cup cream of wheat 1/2 cup all purpose flour 1 teaspoon salt 2 Tablespoons baking soda Directions Preheat oven to 350 Pour oil into cast iron skillet and place in preheted oven In one bowl combine water buttermilk and egg In second bowl combine cream of wheat,flour,salt and baking powder Add wet ingredients and dry together and mix Pour hot oil over batter and lightly stir Pour mixture back into hot ioron skillet and place in oven for 30-45 minutes Cool before serving

Cabbage and Sausage Ingredients 1 lb kielbasa smoked sausage 1 1/2 tbsps olive oil, divided 1 medium onion, chopped 3 garlic cloves, minced 1 medium head cabbage, cored and chopped into 1-inch pieces (about 2 lbs) 3/4 tsp kosher salt, plus more to taste 1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper 1 tsp red wine vinegar Instructions Halve the kielbasa lengthwise and then slice it into 1/2-inch pieces. Heat a large deep skillet or dutch oven over medium heat.  Add 1/2 tablespoon oil and the kielbasa. Toss to coat and then cook until browned, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer the kielbasa to a plate. Return the pan to the stove and reduce the heat to medium low. Add the remaining tablespoon of oil and the onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion has softened. Add the garlic, cabbage, salt, and pepper. Toss well to combine. Cover and cook, stirring every 4-5 minutes until the cabbage is wilted, about 12 minutes. Stir in the vinegar and return the kielbasa to the pot. Stir and cover for about 3 more minutes, until the cabbage is tender and the kielbasa is hot. Taste and add salt, if needed. Enjoy! Notes The original recipe is written with turkey sausage. If that's your preference, it will work nicely in this recipe. My family prefers traditional kielbasa, so that is our choice for this dish. Good morning fellow sufferers, I have been applying the combined cream and gel morning and night. I can sleep with sheets or duvet over my feet with no problems. I can now sleep through the night without the fire pain in my feet and the cold pain in my hands. I wake up I take a B12 injection every other day along with co-factors and several vitamins. I take Pregabalin 3 times a day and Duloxatene twice a day. I can sit here and write my post with no pain in my hands and feet. I have slight pins & needle feeling in my hands and feet but I can live with that. My hands right now have a soft sandpaper texture feeling, but this changes to slight numbness on occasions. I don't think I will ever be back to normal but as long as I can keep the fire and cold pain at bay with the aid of these products I am happy. I really hope it helps you has it has me. Thank you for reading my post. Good luck to my fellow sufferers and hopefully you all can achieve a point when you can say I have got my pain under control
